The most popular choice now is the neck pillow. It's in the shape of a horseshoe, to help you put the two ends on your shoulders and lay your head around the comfy curved portion. These contoured cushions were introduced on the market, simply because they give your neck the support it needs if you need to acquire some rest and you don't have an effective bed to rest on.

Travel pillows with neck support are made with assorted filling materials like standard cushion, soft beads, high-tech foam, and others. Additionally, it comes in different fabric covers including cotton, suede and velour. If you are worried about very limited space for storage and would really like something that's easy to pack, additionally they come in inflatable form.

However, if space isn't a problem, you are able to choose a miniature rectangular pillow that has ultra-comfortable materials. Some that are designed for traveling are even created using 100% organic materials like cotton, wool, or bamboo. This works best for you if your main concern is having full travel comfort and hypo-allergenic materials.

